name: 1. API Modeling v1
description:
Recommended to configure an Environment with your commonly used org and host, as well as your auth configuration.

This collection also leverages URL params heavily, so toggle those on to see how the URL is constructed.

requests.name: Method Doc Template (standalone)
requests.description: For method details pages. This is the default template and cannot be modified (create a custom template instead)

requests.name: Show generated POSTMAN template
requests.description: Load this in a browser to see your docs (and view-source)

requests.name: Method Doc Template (cms)
requests.description: This template trims away the kinds of things that are provided by a CMS like Drupal, such as fonts, header, sidebar, etc.

requests.name: Add custom token authentication
requests.description: Pre-supply a key value if you want developers to use a sample key. If not, you can leave the value empty.

requests.name: Update POSTMAN template
Show generated HTML docs index
requests.description: Load this in a browser to see your docs.

requests.name: Index Doc Template (standalone)
requests.description: See the template for generating the doc index page. Note that this is a default template and cannot be modified (create a custom template instead).

requests.name: Update an API model
requests.description: Use a partial PUT to update any top-level field. If updating an array, send the complete array.

requests.data:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<application xmlns="http://wadl.dev.java.net/2009/02" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:apigee="http://api.apigee.com/wadl/2010/07/" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://wadl.dev.java.net/2009/02 http://apigee.com/schemas/wadl-schema.xsd http://api.apigee.com/wadl/2010/07/ http://apigee.com/schemas/apigee-wadl-extensions.xsd">
   <resources base="https://{host}/{version}/organizations/{orgId}/apimodels" apigee:displayName="API Modeling API">
        <param type="xsd:string" style="template" name="host" default="api.enterprise.apigee.com"/>
        <param type="xsd:string" style="template" name="version" default="v1"/>
      <!-->API Resources<-->
      <resource path="/">
         <param name="orgId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>Organization name.</doc>
         </param>
         <method apigee:displayName="Get APIs" id="apis_get" name="GET">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">API</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Returns the descriptions of all APIs in the organization.</doc>
         </method>
      </resource>
      <resource path="/">
         <param name="baseUrl" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>e.g. api.enterprise.apigee.com</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="orgId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>Organization name.</doc>
         </param>
         <method apigee:displayName="Create API" id="api_post" name="POST">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">API</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Adds an API resource, with a name and a description. The actual API description is added using a
                    different set of methods that are described in the following sections.</doc>
            <request>
               <param default="application/json" name="Content-Type" required="true" style="header" type="xsd:string"/>
               <representation>
                  <!-- This section describes the body content, i.e. the payload. -->
                  <!-- Set required to true to indicate the content as mandatory in the Console -->
                  <apigee:payload required="true">
                     <!-- Docs are optional, but recommended. -->
                     <doc>"The name is an API name. e.g. testApi. The description is description of an API."</doc>
                     <!-- Body content. -->
                     <apigee:content><![CDATA[
{
  "name":"",
  "description":""
}]]></apigee:content>
                  </apigee:payload>
               </representation>
            </request>
         </method>
      </resource>
      <resource path="/{apiId}">
         <param name="baseUrl" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>e.g. api.enterprise.apigee.com</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="orgId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>Organization name.</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="apiId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>API name or UUID, e.g., twitter</doc>
         </param>
         <method apigee:displayName="Get API" id="api_get" name="GET">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">API</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Returns the details of an API, such as its name, description, list of revisions and metadata.</doc>
         </method>
         <method apigee:displayName="Update API" id="api_put" name="PUT">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">API</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Updates an API resource.</doc>
            <request>
               <param default="application/json" name="Content-Type" required="true" style="header" type="xsd:string"/>
               <representation>
                  <!-- This section describes the body content, i.e. the payload. -->
                  <!-- Set required to true to indicate the content as mandatory in the Console -->
                  <apigee:payload required="true">
                     <!-- Docs are optional, but recommended. -->
                     <doc>"The name is an API name. e.g. testApi. The description is description of an API."</doc>
                     <!-- Body content. -->
                     <apigee:content><![CDATA[{
                                   	"name":"",
                                   	"description":""
                                  	}]]></apigee:content>
                  </apigee:payload>
               </representation>
            </request>
         </method>
         <method apigee:displayName="Delete API" id="api_delete" name="DELETE">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">API</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Deletes an API resource and all its associated data.</doc>
         </method>
      </resource>
      
      <!-->API Revisions Resources<-->
      <resource path="/{apiId}/revisions">
         <param name="baseUrl" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>e.g. api.enterprise.apigee.com</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="orgId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>Organization name.</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="apiId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>API name or UUID, e.g., twitter</doc>
         </param>
         <method apigee:displayName="Get API Revisions" id="api_revisions_get" name="GET">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">API Revision</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Returns the descriptions of all API revisions of given api id in the organization.</doc>
         </method>
         <method apigee:displayName="Import an API description" id="import_api_post" name="POST">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">API</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Imports the given API description to the API Modeling repository.</doc>
            <request>
               <param name="action" required="true" style="query" type="xsd:string" default="import">
                  <doc>Import/Export API description.</doc>
               </param>
               <param name="format" required="true" style="query" type="xsd:string" default="WADL">
                  <doc>Format of the API description.</doc>
               </param>
               <param name="Content-Type" required="true" style="header" type="xsd:string" default="application/xml">
                  <doc>The format of the description you're importing.</doc>
               </param>
               <representation mediaType="application/xml">
                  <apigee:payload>
                     <apigee:content><![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<application xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:apigee="http://api.apigee.com/wadl/2010/07/" xmlns="http://wadl.dev.java.net/2009/02" xmlns:t="urn:simplegeo:simplegeoresponse" xsi:schemaLocation="http://wadl.dev.java.net/2009/02 http://apigee.com/schemas/wadl-schema.xsd http://api.apigee.com/wadl/2010/07/ http://apigee.com/schemas/apigee-wadl-extensions.xsd">
	<resources base="https://api.enterprise.apigee.com/v1" apigee:displayName="Apigee Enterprise API">
	<!-- API Products -->
		<resource path="organizations/{org_name}/apiproducts">
			<param name="org_name" type="xsd:string" style="template" required="true">
			<doc>A specific organization.</doc>
			</param>
				<method id="listApiProduct" name="GET" apigee:displayName="List API Products">
					<apigee:tags>
					<apigee:tag primary="true">API Products</apigee:tag>
					</apigee:tags>
					<apigee:authentication required="true"/>
					<apigee:example url="organizations/{org_name}/apiproducts"/>
					<doc apigee:url="http://apigee.com/docs/api/api_methods/4-list-api-products">Use the GET method
					to list all of the API products in an organization.
					</doc>
					<request>
						<param name="expand" type="xsd:string" style="query" default="false"/>
					</request>
				</method>
		</resource>
	</resources> 
</application>]]></apigee:content>
                  </apigee:payload>
               </representation>
            </request>
         </method>
      </resource>
      <!-->Current API Revision Resource<-->
      <resource path="/{apiId}/revisions/current">
         <param name="baseUrl" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>e.g. api.enterprise.apigee.com</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="orgId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>Organization name.</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="apiId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>API name or UUID, e.g., twitter</doc>
         </param>
         <method apigee:displayName="Get Current API Revision" id="api_current_revision_get" name="GET">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">API Revision</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Returns the description of the current revision of the API specified by {apiId}.</doc>
         </method>
      </resource>
      <!-->Latest API Revision Resource<-->
      <resource path="/{apiId}/revisions/latest">
         <param name="baseUrl" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>e.g. api.enterprise.apigee.com</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="orgId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>Organization name.</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="apiId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>API name or UUID, e.g., twitter</doc>
         </param>
         <method apigee:displayName="Get Latest API Revision" id="api_latest_revision_get" name="GET">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">API Revision</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Returns the description of the latest revision of the API specified by {apiId}.</doc>
         </method>
      </resource>
      <resource path="/{apiId}/revisions">
         <param name="baseUrl" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>e.g. api.enterprise.apigee.com</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="orgId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>Organization name.</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="apiId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>API name or UUID, e.g., twitter</doc>
         </param>
         <method apigee:displayName="Create API Revision" id="api_revision_post" name="POST">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">API Revision</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Adds a new revision of an API.</doc>
            <request>
               <param default="application/json" name="Content-Type" required="false" style="header" type="xsd:string"/>
               <representation>
                  <!-- This section describes the body content, i.e. the payload. -->
                  <!-- Set required to true to indicate the content as mandatory in the Console -->
                  <apigee:payload required="true">
                     <!-- Docs are optional, but recommended. -->
                     <doc>"baseUrl is Valid Base URL. e.g. http://testApi.com. description is Description of a
                                Revision."</doc>
                     <!-- Body content. -->
                     <apigee:content><![CDATA[{

                                  	"baseUrl":"",

                                  	"description":""

                                 	}]]></apigee:content>
                  </apigee:payload>
                  <param name="inherit" type="xsd:string" style="query" required="false" default="json">
                     <doc>Revision number or UUID, which needs to be inherited</doc>
                  </param>
               </representation>
            </request>
         </method>
      </resource>
      <resource path="/{apiId}/revisions/{revisionId}">
         <param name="baseUrl" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>e.g. api.enterprise.apigee.com</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="orgId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>Organization name.</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="apiId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>API name or UUID, e.g., twitter</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="revisionId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>Revision number or UUID, e.g., 1</doc>
         </param>
         <method apigee:displayName="Get API Revision" id="api_revision_get" name="GET">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">API Revision</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Returns the details of a particular revision of an API.</doc>
            <request>
               <param name="verbose" type="xsd:string" style="query" required="false" default="json">
                  <doc>Values can be yes or no. When enabled i.e. passed as a query param with value yes, this
                            will return underlying resources and oprations.</doc>
               </param>
            </request>
         </method>
         <method apigee:displayName="Update API Revision" id="api_revision_put" name="PUT">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">API Revision</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Updates a particular revision of an API.</doc>
            <request>
               <param default="application/json" name="Content-Type" required="false" style="header" type="xsd:string"/>
               <representation>
                  <apigee:payload required="true">
                     <doc>"baseUrl is Valid Base URL. e.g. http://testApi.com. description is Description of a
                                Revision."</doc>
                     <apigee:content><![CDATA[{

                                  	"baseUrl":"",

                                  	"description":""

                                 	}]]></apigee:content>
                  </apigee:payload>
                  <param name="baseUrl" type="xsd:string" style="query" required="false" default="json">
                     <doc>This is base url of an API revision</doc>
                  </param>
               </representation>
            </request>
         </method>
         <method apigee:displayName="Delete API Revision" id="api_revision_delete" name="DELETE">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">API Revision</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Deletes a particular revision of an API and all its associated data.</doc>
         </method>
      </resource>
      <!-- Resource element resources -->
      <resource path="/{apiId}/revisions/{revisionId}/resources/">
         <param name="baseUrl" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>e.g. api.enterprise.apigee.com</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="orgId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>Organization name.</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="apiId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>API name or UUID, e.g., twitter</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="revisionId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>Revision number or UUID, e.g., 1</doc>
         </param>
         <method apigee:displayName="Create Resource" id="resource_post" name="POST">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">Resource</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Adds a new resource for an revision.</doc>
            <request>
               <param default="application/json" name="Content-Type" required="false" style="header" type="xsd:string"/>
               <representation>
                  <apigee:payload required="true">
                     <doc>Requires name and path. Other fields are optional.</doc>
                     <!-- Body content. -->
                     <apigee:content><![CDATA[{
    "name" : "console",
    "description" : "Console Resource",
    "path" : "/consoles/{name}",
    "parameters" : [
        {
            "name" : "mediaType",
            "type" : "query",
            "description" : "Sets the media type of the resource",
            "default" : "XML",
            "required" : "true"
        },
        {
            "name" : "param2",
            "type" : "header",
            "description" : "…",
            "default" : "…",
            "required" : "false"
        }
    ]
}]]></apigee:content>
                  </apigee:payload>
               </representation>
            </request>
         </method>
         <method apigee:displayName="Get Resources" id="resources_get" name="GET">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">Resource</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Returns a list of all resources for a given API revsion.</doc>
         </method>
         
      </resource>
      <resource path="/{apiId}/revisions/{revisionId}/resources/{resourceId}">
         <param name="baseUrl" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>e.g. api.enterprise.apigee.com</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="orgId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>Organization name.</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="apiId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>API name or UUID, e.g., twitter</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="revisionId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>Revision number or UUID, e.g., 1</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="resourceId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>Resource name or UUID, e.g., displayTweets</doc>
         </param>
         <method apigee:displayName="Get Resource" id="resource_get" name="GET">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">Resource</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Returns a resource for a given resourceId.</doc>
         </method>
         <method apigee:displayName="Update Resource" id="resource_put" name="PUT">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">Resource</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Updates a particular resource of an revision.</doc>
            <request>
               <param default="application/json" name="Content-Type" required="false" style="header" type="xsd:string"/>
               <representation>
                  <apigee:payload required="true">
                     <doc>Requires name and path. Other fields are optional.</doc>
                     <apigee:content><![CDATA[{
    "name" : "apiconsole",
    "description" : "API Console Resource",
    "path" : "/apiconsoles/{name}"
}]]></apigee:content>
                  </apigee:payload>
               </representation>
            </request>
         </method>
         <method apigee:displayName="Delete Resource" id="resource_delete" name="DELETE">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">Resource</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Deletes a particular resource of an revision and all its associated data.</doc>
         </method>
       
      </resource>
      <resource path="/{apiId}/revisions/{revisionId}/resources/{resourceId}/operations/">
         <param name="baseUrl" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>e.g. api.enterprise.apigee.com</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="orgId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>Organization name.</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="apiId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>API name or UUID, e.g., twitter</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="revisionId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>Revision number or UUID, e.g., 1</doc>
         </param>
         <param name="resourceId" required="true" style="template" type="xsd:string">
            <doc>Resource name or UUID, e.g., displayTweets</doc>
         </param>
         <method apigee:displayName="Create Operation" id="operation_post" name="POST">
            <apigee:tags>
               <apigee:tag primary="true">Operation</apigee:tag>
            </apigee:tags>
            <apigee:authentication required="true"/>
            <doc>Adds a new operations for a resource.</doc>
            <request>
               <param default="application/json" name="Content-Type" required="false" style="header" type="xsd:string"/>
               <representation>
                  <apigee:payload required="true">
                     <doc>Requires name and verb. Other fields are optional.</doc>
                     <apigee:content><![CDATA[{
    "name" : "addOperation",
    "description" : "Method to add operation",
    "verb" : "POST",
    "authSchemes" : ["OAUTH2IMPLICITGRANT"],
}]]></apigee:content>
                  </apigee:payload>
               </representation>
            </request>

                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </header>

                                <div class="method_data title">Method</div>
                                <div class="method_data description">Description</div>
                            </div>
                               {{#operations}}

                                      </div>
                                      <div class="method_data description">

                                      </div>
                                  </div>
                            {{/operations}}
                        </div>
                    {{/if}}
                {{/each}}
                {{/each}}
            </div>
        </div>

        <script type="text/javascript" src="http://docs.lapigee.com/docs/js/handlebars.js"></script>
        <script src="http://docs.lapigee.com/docs/js/resources_json.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
        <script>
            $(function() {
                $("a[data-role='method_name']").each(function() {
                    var elementVal = $(this).text();
                    if (elementVal.length > 20) {
                        elementVal = elementVal.substring(0,12) +"...";
                        $(this).text(elementVal);
                    }
                });
                $("p[data-role='resource_path']").each(function() {
                    var elementVal = $(this).text();
                    if (elementVal.length > 20) {
                        elementVal = elementVal.substring(0,12) +"...";
                        $(this).text(elementVal);
                    }
                });
                $('div#index_container').show();    
            });
        </script>
    </body>
</html>]]></apigee:content>
